      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DISORDERLY (1) shapes well for this on his head turning win a few runs back, getting around Grafton over 350m in 19.84 then hitting the frame in both runs since. Has the ability and looks a key chance again. GO GRACIE GO (2) held her own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only 0.8 lengths (16.69) behind Ding Ding Harrow at this track. Overdue and is among the main hopes. ARNIE FERRARI (5) finished in the placings last time but could not have been more impressive three back in his solid 16.56 win at this track over 300m. Rates a leading chance if runs up to recent winning time.",
